3.1 File Input/Output

* Low-level (byte)
➡ FileInputStream / FileOutputStream — read/write bytes from/to files.

* Character
➡ FileReader / FileWriter — simple for text, but they use the platform default encoding
  (so prefer InputStreamReader/OutputStreamWriter with explicit charset).

* Convenience (NIO)
➡ java.nio.file.Files has many convenient methods (Files.readAllLines,
  Files.newBufferedReader, Files.write, etc.) and supports charset directly.
